<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871224-0056 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Meridian Bancorp</HL><DD> 12/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MRDNTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BANKS, THRIFT INSTITUTIONS (BNK) </IN><TEXT>   Meridian Bancorp said it received approval from the Delaware Banking Commissioner and the Pennsylvania Banking Department to acquire Delaware Trust Co.    The approvals clear the way for completion of the $196 million stock transaction next month, when Delaware's new interstate banking legislation takes effect. Reading, Pa.-based Meridian, the fifth largest bank holding concern in Pennsylvania, has assets of $6.8 billion. It also has corporate-lending offices in the Baltimore area. Delaware Trust is based in Wilmington, Del. </TEXT></DOC>